OL,3,CLong Covid 'leaves traces in the
OL,4,Cblood' that could lead to successful
OL,5,Ctreatment
OL,7,FHow this activation happened depended
OL,8,Fon the type of symptoms they mainly
OL,9,Fhad, for example fatigue or brain fog.
OL,11,FThe research, led by Imperial College
OL,12,FLondon, suggests existing drugs which
OL,13,Fmodulate the body's immune system
OL,14,Fcould be helpful in treating long
OL,15,FCovid and should be investigated in
OL,16,Ffuture research.
OL,18,FProfessor Peter Openshaw, from
OL,19,FImperial's National Heart and Lung
OL,20,FInstitute, said long Covid is "very
OL,21,Fhard" to diagnose and treat.
