OL,3,CLong Covid 'leaves traces in the
OL,4,Cblood' that could lead to successful
OL,5,Ctreatment
OL,7,FDr Felicity Liew, from Imperial's
OL,8,FNational Heart and Lung Institute,
OL,9,Fsaid: "Our findings indicate that
OL,10,Fcomplement activation and myeloid
OL,11,Finflammation could be a common feature
OL,12,Fof long Covid after hospitalisation,
OL,13,Fregardless of symptom type.
OL,15,F"It is unusual to find evidence of
OL,16,Fongoing complement activation several
OL,17,Fmonths after acute infection has
OL,18,Fresolved, suggesting that long Covid
OL,19,Fsymptoms are a result of active
OL,20,Finflammation."
